The general reporting requirement would provide that every registered broker-dealer that carries accounts for
large traders, or other persons for whom records must be maintained, shall electronically report transactions in
machine-readable form and in accordance with instructions issued by the Commission. Transaction reports would
be required to contain all elements of information for transactions effected through accounts carried by such broker-dealer
for large traders and other persons for whom records must be maintained, which equal or exceed the reporting activity
level. The Commission continues to propose that transaction reports be transmitted through the existing electronic
bluesheet system.
 The special reporting requirement for trades of ``unidentified large traders,'' has been reorganized without changes
into paragraph (e)(5) of the reproposed rule. 



